<br>
At the Seattle Fan Faire questions were posed about the petition to a panel of devs, who acknowledged that they were aware of the petition and had read it, but made no specific comments on issues due to the larger caster balancing issue. <br>
<br>
Alan also posted a note that petition formats were not productive and that a simpler format would be much better, so we sent off our points in a simple bullet list. Some things were discussed in private emails -- sorry I can't say what they were.<br>
<br>
Casters Realm was kind enough to post our petition drive as news, and as such, we got a flood of responses both good and bad. Signatures grew. The whole metadiscussion of petitions even drew the attention of Woody Hearn who made a funny /GU comic about the topic.<br>
<br>
Once the frenzy died down, discussion continued, and Sobe decided that the petition had met its goal of attracting the attention of the EQ Live team and that they were fully aware of the issue. Caster balancing has taken over as the larger concern, but we were reassured that we would be looked at, and Rich Waters did say that priests would be next after the initial pet class changes.<br>
<br>
When the team had finalized the pet changes, Waters took to the forums and posted the imminent changes so that the mage, necromancer, and enchanter communities could give feedback, and I suspect he will do the same for clerics, druids, and shamans on our respective forums when they are ready. At least we do know they have some plans for "more flexible healing" -- whatever that means. :D<br>
<br>
After the discussions, the earring quest, and the POTC quest (not to mention spellcasting mobs and focus items) we are waiting for good news. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugippah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gippah</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/02 2:43:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27582.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://destroy.austin.tx.us/diary/cgi-bin/random.cgi WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: State of the Druid petition response</span><hr size=1> yer dum <p><br>
